						<summary>

						<p>At the entrance of the natural cave east of the rock known as Āḷuruṭṭimalai.</p>						

						<p>Māṟavarmaṉ Sundarapāṇḍya I. acc. 1216 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The date portion of this inscription is lost.</p>						

						<p>This epigraph seems to record a grant of land in Periyapaḷḷivayal as <hi rend="italic">paḷḷichchandam</hi> to Nāyaṉār Tirumāṉaimalai Āḻvār, by Pāmbaiyurūḍaiyāṉ Śeṅguḍi Āṉaina[ḍi] (?) tēnar perumagaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Gaṅgādarar, a merchant. It mentions Kanakachandra Paṇḍita and his disciple Danmadēva Āchāryaṉ.</p>						

						<p>Text published in Inscription (Texts) of the Pudukkottai State, No. 474. The text is, however, published here in view of some differences in the reading. </p>						

						</summary>
